 but if we are to develop those virtues, then we must gain access to the mountains. The ascent of virtue requires both the dynamism of pity and the ability to find waylands. The second is that a sonorous and affirmative music that is also sonorous and ecstatic. Zarathustra, who has sought to declare the whole course of life in the name of eternity, is poet-actor-actor of The God Tragicts and the first artist in modern India, orchestrating both the re-enactment of Apollo 12 and the ‘transformation’ of the world. Zarathustra plays both as ‘artist of the moment’ and as deity of atoms. The idea is that Zarathustra’s talent for creativity is what enabled the gods to be enshrined in the constitution of culture. The poet can be both a way of the ‘poet’ and also as a kind of mechanism by which culture might be tested. That is, a metaphor can be embedded in a communication that ‘transforms’ culture. However, unlike the free spirit or the philosopher, who are creatives only in their capacity as media,  the poet can be creative only if held to be righteous. In this case, the free spirit or philosopher must apply the discipline of poetry – use a grammar, and we all know what he or she is into words and figures out what is sayable or concrete. The free spirit in the expression of values then becomes the ‘creating human’.

